  "texts": [
    "By recognizing this, we can appreciate that the interactions between individuals, technology, and social systems have always been dynamic and evolving.",
    "This perspective helps us understand that the challenges and opportunities presented by generative AI in scientific authorship are part of a continuous evolution, rather than a fundamentally new disruption.",
    "Traditional notions of authorship in the modern era involve human intellectual contribution, originality, and accountability.",
    "However, when AI systems generate text, it complicates the attribution process.",
    "Who should be credited as the author-the human who directed the AI, the developers of the AI, or the AI itself?"
  ],
